# Local dev / e2e bootstrap for amberflo-provider.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` at the repo root and fill in the values.
# `.env` is gitignored — do NOT commit real credentials.
#
# The Taskfile reads `.env` via the top-level `dotenv: ['.env']` key, so
# any task you run from this repo sees these variables in its
# environment. `task test:create-amberflo-credentials` consumes them to
# provision a Kubernetes Secret named `amberflo-credentials` in the
# `amberflo-provider-system` namespace of the kind cluster.
#
# The provider binary also reads AMBERFLO_API_KEY directly as a
# second-choice fallback when the configured Secret file is absent — see
# `loadAPIKey` in cmd/amberflo-provider/main.go. This makes `go run ./...`
# and sandbox smoke tests Just Work without needing a kubeconfig.

# Required — the X-API-KEY value for your Amberflo **SANDBOX** org.
# The `test:setup` and `e2e` tasks target https://app.amberflo.io with
# this key against live Amberflo; every reconcile writes real customer
# records. Never put a production key in this file.
# Create / rotate at https://app.amberflo.io (Settings → API Keys).
AMBERFLO_API_KEY=
